items.title: Twins club 7 homers as Gibson blanks Padres
items.summary: The Twins clubbed a season-high seven homers to back another strong outing by Kyle Gibson in a 16-0 win over the Padres on Tuesday night at Target Field. Minnesota increased its lead for the second American League Wild Card spot to 1 1/2 games, pending the result of Tuesday's Astros-Angels game.

items.title: 'Pen Power: Crew shares workload in key win
items.summary: For the first time in three weeks, the pennant-hungry Brewers managed to take care of business against a team below the break-even point.

items.title: Stanton's 3rd OF assist halts Phils' walk-off
items.summary: Having scrounged back from a 7-2 deficit in the final three innings, the Phillies were poised on the doorstep of a comeback victory with the bases loaded down by two.
